Question 2

Make a single plot with boxplots of the average medicare payments by DRG code. What do you notice from the plots?

ggplot(data=drg,aes(DRG.Definition,Average.Medicare.Payments,col=DRG.Definition),xlab="DRG code", ylab="Average.Medicare.Payments")+
  ggtitle("Boxplot of Average.Medicare.Payments and DRGs")+
  geom_boxplot()+
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 8),legend.position="none",plot.title = element_text(size=15,hjust = 0.5))+
  coord_flip()

The boxplot shows that the majority average medicare payments is between 0 to 25000, while there are also some codes with the lower quantile above 25000, such as 207,329, 853 and 870.

Question 5

Make a function to calculate the mean, median, and standard deviation of the average medicare payments for each DRG code column.

code<-distinct(drg,DRG.Definition)
calc<-function(x){
  c<-drg %>%
    filter(DRG.Definition==x) %>%
    group_by(DRG.Definition) %>%
    summarise(mean=mean(Average.Medicare.Payments),
              median=median(Average.Medicare.Payments),
              sd=sd(Average.Medicare.Payments))
  c
}

## Use for loop
g<-NULL
for(i in code$DRG.Definition){
  g<-bind_rows(g,calc(i))
}

## make the function to figure out the max and min of these statistics.
mi<-function(x){
  a<-g %>%
  summarise(max_name=DRG.Definition[which.max(x)],
            max_value=max(x),
            min_name=DRG.Definition[which.min(x)],
            min_value=min(x))
a
}
max_min<-bind_rows(mi(g$mean),mi(g$median),mi(g$sd))
max_min

870 - SEPTICEMIA OR SEVERE SEPSIS W MV 96+ HOURS has the max mean, median, and sd which are 41899.43,38789.43 and 11766.81. 310 - CARDIAC ARRHYTHMIA & CONDUCTION DISORDERS W/O CC/MCC has the minimum mean value of 2876.016 and sd of 880.665, while 313 - CHEST PAIN has the minimum median at 2587.425.

Question 7

Make a function to return the provider in each state with the most expensive average medicare payments for the DRG code 870 - SEPTICEMIA OR SEVERE SEPSIS W MV 96+ HOURS.

state<-function(x){
  x %>%
    filter(DRG.Definition=="870 - SEPTICEMIA OR SEVERE SEPSIS W MV 96+ HOURS")%>%
    select(Provider.State,Provider.Name,Average.Medicare.Payments) %>%
    arrange(desc(Average.Medicare.Payments)) %>% 
    head(n = 1)
}

drg %>% 
  group_by(Provider.State) %>% 
  do(state(.))

Find the most expensive provider in New York.

drg %>% 
  group_by(Provider.State) %>%
  filter(Provider.State=="NY") %>%
  do(state(.))

The most expensive provider in New York is WESTCHESTER MEDICAL CENTER with a payment of 107456.2.

My function to the name of the most expensive provider in New York for other codes.

expen<-function(x){
  expensive<-drg %>%
  filter(DRG.Definition==x)%>%
  group_by(Provider.State) %>%
  summarise(name=Provider.Name[which.max(Average.Medicare.Payments)],
            payment=max(Average.Medicare.Payments)) %>%
  filter(Provider.State=="NY")
expensive
}
expen("039 - EXTRACRANIAL PROCEDURES W/O CC/MCC")

The most expensive provider of 039 - EXTRACRANIAL PROCEDURES W/O CC/MCC in New York is LONG ISLAND JEWISH MEDICAL CENTER with a payment of 13280.54.

expen("313 - CHEST PAIN")

The most expensive provider of 313 - CHEST PAIN in New York is LINCOLN MEDICAL & MENTAL HEALTH CENTER with a payment of 7255.94.
